. The journey begins in Mettupalayam, a tiny village on the Bhavani River. The first 5 miles are flat, but the engine propels the coaches uphill to a height of 4,363 feet during the next 12 miles. To get to your destination, you may hire taxis, tourist cabs, or auto-rickshaws from practically any place in the city. 4. Emerald Lake in Ooty Emerald Lake is in Tamil Nadu's Nilgiris district, near Emerald village. It is around 25 kilometres from Ooty. The lake is a popular tourist and picnic destination in the area. The lake's numerous fish and local animals are well-known. It is especially well-known for its stunning sunrise and sunset views near the lake. Tourists may also go trekking or mountain biking near the lake to better understand the surroundings. Ooty's Emerald Lake is ideal for nature enthusiasts. Tourists often visit for the stunning panoramic charm of the lake and the surrounding lush green Nilgiri hills and tea estates. Eucalyptus tea is well-known for its powerful flavour; the greatest items may be purchased here. Emerald Lake is accessible by vehicle on the way to the Avalanche Dam. There is no direct transport connection from Ooty or any other large city to the lake. 5. Ooty Lake in Ooty Ooty Lake, also known as Ooty Boathouse, is in the Nilgiris area of Ooty. Ooty Lake is one of the most beautiful and interesting places to visit. Ooty Lake is 65 acres in size, and its foundation was established in 1824 by John Sullivan, the Collector of Coimbatore. It is great for those who are interested in photography. The lake is full of gorgeous water birds with the unique Nilgiri mountain ranges in the background. The major feature of the lake is the boathouse, which offers paddle boats, motorboats, and boats, and many visitors come here to enjoy these boating experiences. A garden, a miniature railroad, and an amusement park are available. Horseback riding will undoubtedly spring to mind during your visit to Ooty. Horse riding in Ooty is enjoyable and provides a